{
  "doc_id": "25405",
  "text": "In all high-temperature processes, radiation is dominant mode of heat transfer [CITATION_1] . In contemporary three-dimensional mathematical models of combustion systems, the following models of thermal radiation are usually used: six-flux model (SFM), discrete ordinates model (DOM), spherical harmonics model (SHM), discrete transfer model (DTM), Monte Carlo model (MCM), and Hottel's zonal model (HZM) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . One of the main characteristics of the radiation model is its accuracy of determination of radiative energy source term and radiative wall fluxes.",
